The body was discovered by women traders who had gone to wash sweet potatoes. [Courtesy]  A two-year-old boy drowned in a well under unclear circumstances at Upper Kanyadawa village, Kowidi sub-location in Rachuonyo East sub-county.  The body of Gregory Otieno was found in a well located at a construction site near Kadongo trading centre along Oyugis-Kisumu road.  The body was discovered by women traders who had gone to wash sweet potatoes.  Assistant Chief Michael Aoro said the child drowned when his parents were away.  Kisumu County calls for collaboration to revive tourism sector  Lake Victoria tragedy: Eight bodies retrieved as search enters day three  Sh580m water project in Oyugis to serve 73,000 households   42-year-old fisherman drowns in Lake Victoria Police have launched investigations into the matter. [James Omoro, Standard]  “Nobody knows who was taking care of the child. Let parents be responsible by ensuring there is someone attending to their children when they are away,” said Aoro.  He said the police had launched investigations into the matter.  The body was moved to Okita Nursing Home Morgue for postmortem examination.   Shot In The Arm: Kisumu County set to roll out Covid-19 vaccination exercise  New Look Kisumu: Personal cars banned from parking along Oginga Odinga street, order given by county  Hundreds of structures demolished in Kisumu demolished by bulldozers belonging to Kenya Railways By Julius Chepkwony | 14 hours ago By Harold Odhiambo | 1 day ago By Harold Odhiambo | 1 day ago By Edwin Nyarangi | 1 day ago